INSERT INTO public.questions (exam_id, subject_id, topic_id, year, paper, question_text, option_1, option_2, option_3, option_4, correct_option, explanation, difficulty) VALUES
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'For a long pipe carrying liquid from one reservoir to another, at the exit section of the pipe, the energy grade line will', 'lie at a distance (v²/2g) above the liquid surface', 'meet the liquid substance', 'lie at a distance (v²/4g) below the liquid surface', 'lie at a distance (v²/2g) below the liquid surface', 1, 'At exit, EGL is v²/2g above the free surface (since HGL is at surface).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Match the following statements for the critical buckling load of a column of length L with modulus of elasticity E, and moment of inertia I. A. Column with pinned joints at both end. B. Column with fixed at both ends. C. Column with fixed at one end and pinned at another end. D. Column with fixed at one end and free at another end.', 'A-4, B-2, C-1, D-3', 'A-1, B-2, C-3, D-4', 'A-3, B-2, C-1, D-4', 'A-2, B-3, C-4, D-1', 2, 'Pinned-pinned: 1; Fixed-fixed: 2; Fixed-pinned: 3; Fixed-free: 4.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Total suspended solids in a strong sewage in PPM', '100', '200', '350', '500', 3, 'Strong sewage has TSS ≈ 350 mg/l.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6'::uuid, '4cf00bbd-c0d6-49dd-88a5-505bae0ef9ab'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'If the formation level of a highway has a uniform gradient for a particular length, and the ground is also having a longitudinal slope, the earthwork CANNOT be calculated by', 'Trapezoidal formula', 'Mid-section formula', 'Prismoidal formula', 'Centre line method', 4, 'Centre line method is for walls, not earthwork.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'For a two-dimensional generalized system, how many equilibrium equations are available?', '2', '1', '3', '4', 3, 'For 2D, three equations: ΣFx, ΣFy, ΣM.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'What is the correct decreasing order of the following materials with respect to their Poisson''s ratio? A. Copper B. Steel C. Tungsten', 'A, C, B', 'A, B, C', 'B, C, A', 'C, B, A', 2, 'Poisson''s ratios: Copper ≈0.35, Steel ≈0.3, Tungsten ≈0.28. So A > B > C.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Examine the correctness of following statements. A. In whole circle bearing system, the bearing of a line varies from zero to 90 degrees B. The angle of dip at the equator is zero degree C. French cross staff is used to set out angles of either 45 or 90 degrees D. In quadrantal bearing system, the bearing of a line varies from zero to 360 degrees Choose the correct option', 'Only D is correct', 'Only B is correct', 'A and D are correct', 'B and C are correct', 4, 'A false (0-360), B true (dip zero at equator), C true (French cross staff can set 45° and 90°), D false (0-90).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Settling velocity of a spherical body is expressed by', 'Newton''s law', 'Reynolds law', 'Stokes law', 'Darcey''s law', 3, 'Stokes law for small particles in laminar flow.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424'::uuid, '1bba627d-75a7-47e9-8413-f09905572b33'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following compound contributes to strength development of cement concrete after 28 days ?', 'Tetraalcium alumino-ferrite', 'Dicalcium silicate', 'Tricalcium aluminate', 'Tricalcium silicate', 2, 'C₂S contributes to later strength (after 28 days).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following is used as coagulant in treatment of water ?', 'Al₂SO₄·8H₂O', 'Al₂(SO₄)₂·18H₂O', 'Al₂(SO₄)₃·18H₂O', 'Al₂(SO₄)₃·8H₂O', 3, 'Alum is Al₂(SO₄)₃·18H₂O.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419'::uuid, '4002ff85-6eee-4cd3-8c35-1d7039df2745'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'What is the relationship between Poisson''s ratio and axial strain ?', 'Poisson''s ratio is directly proportional to axial strain.', 'Poisson''s ratio is inversely proportional to axial strain.', 'Poisson''s ratio is inversely proportional to the squared of axial strain.', 'Poisson''s ratio is directly proportional to the squared of the axial strain.', Unknown, 'Poisson''s ratio is a material constant, independent of strain for linear elastic materials. None of the options.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The compressive strength of a second class brick is', '10.5 N/mm²', '12 N/mm²', '7.0 N/mm²', '4.0 N/mm²', 3, 'Second class bricks have minimum compressive strength of 7 N/mm².', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The art and science of collecting information about an object or an area without being the direct contact is called', 'Compass survey', 'Chain survey', 'Levelling survey', 'Remote sensing survey', 4, 'Remote sensing.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The coefficient of discharge venturimetre, lies between', '0.50 to 0.75', '0.3 to 0.45', '0.75 to 0.95', '0.95 to 1.0', 4, 'Cd for venturimeter is typically 0.95 to 0.99.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b'::uuid, '5005286a-c8a9-4f38-a12f-46a61fd65689'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The disease Dysentery is caused due to the presence of organism in water', 'Entamoeba histolytica', 'Salmonella typhi', 'Vibrio cholerae', 'Virus', 1, 'Dysentery caused by Entamoeba histolytica.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which method is used for balancing the traverse when angular and linear measurements are equally precise ?', 'Simpson''s rule', 'Transit rule', 'Sine rule', 'Bowditch rule', 4, 'Bowditch rule is used when both are equally precise.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The type of glass that consists of fine but solid rods of glass is known as :', 'Fibre glass', 'Laminated glass', 'Heat resistant glass', 'Float glass', 1, 'Fibreglass consists of glass rods.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424'::uuid, '1bba627d-75a7-47e9-8413-f09905572b33'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following expressions is required to calculate the strength of shear reinforcement for single bar or single group of parallel bars, all bent-up at the same cross section ? The characteristic strength and the cross-sectional area of the bent-up bars are given by f_y and A_sv respectively. The angle between the bent-up bar and the axis of the member is given by α.', '0.87 f_y A_sv cos α', '0.87 f_y A_sv sin α', '0.87 f_y A_sv (sin α + cos α)', '0.87 f_y A_sv tan α', 2, 'Vertical component of bent-up bar is sin α, so strength = 0.87 f_y A_sv sin α.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239'::uuid, '880c7ee1-0204-4a42-979f-338ca32f84be'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Under which group the Residential buildings fall, as per NBC ?', 'Group C', 'Group D', 'Group A', 'Group B', 3, 'Residential buildings are Group A.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2'::uuid, '29d611e8-8d9c-48f0-85c3-621cccd58722'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'A horizontal curve is to be designed in a region with a limited space. In this condition which of the followings is/are correct to decrease the radius of the curve ? A. Increase the super elevation B. Decrease the super elevation C. Increase the design speed D. Decrease the design speed Choose the correct option', 'B and C', 'A and C', 'A and D', 'B and D', 3, 'To reduce radius, increase super elevation or decrease speed.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6'::uuid, '4cf00bbd-c0d6-49dd-88a5-505bae0ef9ab'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The unit of payment of cement concrete in lintels is', 'cubic metre', 'kilograms', 'square metre', 'tonne', 1, 'Concrete is measured in cubic metres.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'cd7b170d-eba3-4a13-8b23-3c318071b538'::uuid, '63b1aa41-9022-4bff-b5b8-0aa71ec874fd'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements are correct for the bending strength of a laterally supported steel beam ? A. Bending strength requires elastic section modulus of the cross section for plastic and compact sections. B. Bending strength requires plastic section modulus of the cross section for plastic and compact sections. C. Bending strength requires ultimate stress of the material. D. Bending strength requires yield stress of the material.', 'A and D', 'A and C', 'B and C', 'B and D', 4, 'Plastic and compact sections use plastic modulus and yield stress.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c'::uuid, 'f28c858a-cf0c-482e-a112-8845927e82f4'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Theodolite is used for measuring', 'Vertical angles only', 'Horizontal angles only', 'Horizontal and vertical angles', 'Linear measurements', 3, 'Theodolite measures both horizontal and vertical angles.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990'::uuid, 'ec71764c-6040-47e0-bbc1-9777aafbeec7'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following cannot be the value of absolute pressure of a fluid at any point?', '13 bar', '0', '-10 bar', '2 bar', 3, 'Absolute pressure cannot be negative.', 'medium')
